xpected instance properties.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 2, 8, 55, 53, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'rpl', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 448855152, 'comment_body': 'At the moment we do only have one message to handle, the one that appends logs, and so I think that for now we could just do this inside the runtime.onMessage listener (and defer introducing an abstraction to expand the message that this page will handle to the point where we do have some other actual type of message that this page is meant to handle).

Also, `renderTable` seems a bit misleading as a name for a function that is actually "adding more rows to the table", based on the name one would assume that it would re-render the entire table, which isn't the case.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 2, 9, 0, 3, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'rpl', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 448858089, 'comment_body': 'we should be able to get the row that include the clicked element by just using something like  `event.target.closest("tr[index]")`, this should get the tr element also when event.target is the tr element itself.

