- the row itself (a TR element with the index attribute)
- another arbitrary element that is outside of a row (and in this case we expect closest to return null)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2020, 7, 2, 9, 4, 52, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'rpl', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 448888288, 'comment_body': "This isn't right, when the activity log pages receives a set of logs all at ones (e.g. the one collected in the background page while the activity log page wasn't open yet), this would create rows with the same index (that will be the length of the array of logs received all at once).

